<br>
Never, NEVER listen to the raid organizer.  In fact, as soon as you get to the meeting spot, go to options and turn off any oocs and shouts so you can test your sleuthing skills during the raid with trying to figure out who the raid organizer is in the first place.  Make sure that you emote as much as possible, raid  participants love mimes.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=shadusanator>Shadusanator</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/14/00 8:18:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Dragon Raid Questions</span><hr size=1> Where do I need to look or signup for Dragon raids? I have heard there is a schedule kept somewhere on the web. Im at the propper level and would really like to get started on these.<br>
