 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/17/00 12:38:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How long...</span><hr size=1> Q: How long does it take to organize the raid? (From the point when everyone arrives at the staging point, to when you actually start the raid)<br>
<br>
A: The key to this question is &quot;when everyone arrives at the staging point&quot;.  While organizing the groups does take time, it takes nearly as much time for everyone to get there because of the nature of how little time we normally get to announce the raid.<br>
<br>
The act of organizing involves determining who is present at the raid (classes and levels) and how the groups are going to be built.  This process is slowed by people not showing up on time, sending tells directly to the raid organizers, unexpected departures from the raid, and people goofing off in ooc and shout.<br>
<br>
During the last Naggy raid, Bamana and I acted as a team in putting the groups together.  We used Roger Wilco, which greatly simplified the process.  We are also going to create a raid kit which will be used to collect the participants, build the groups, record loot distribution, and handle any other task we can think of (this is Bam's idea, she's very good at organizing).<br>
<br>
Q: How long does a Dragon raid take from entrance to the dungeon to finish?<br>
<br>
A: I plan 6 hours, but this can vary greatly.  The two longest parts of the raid are the initial organization and the final buffing.  Killing the giants is usually straightforward (if the raid party gets to do it), but deaths to the pullers or other group members can slow this down.  People not staying in position can also slow this down.<br>
<br>
The fight with the dragon should be relatively short, by comparison.  If the fight begins to drag on, then it's usually a sign of insufficient fire power (as was the case with the last Naggy raid).  Depending on success or failure, the corpse recovery can last anywhere from one to three hours.  Hopefully, we'll become good enough at this to minimize the number of deaths. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ullewlifebringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llew Lifebringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/21/00 2:02:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Cleric levels...</span><hr size=1> Tanks of 40th, Casters of 45th...<br>
